  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Navigation Menu Active State Bug\n\nThe navigation menu incorrectly highlights the main page link regardless of which page the user is currently viewing. The active/highlighted state should only apply to the link corresponding to the current page.\n\nRequirements:\n- Investigate current routing and active state logic in the navigation menu component\n- Ensure active state correctly reflects the current route/page\n- Remove hardcoded or default active state on main page link\n- Verify active state updates properly when navigating between pages\n- Test all navigation links to ensure only the current page is highlighted\n- Handle edge cases like nested routes, query parameters, and hash fragments\n- Ensure visual indicator (highlighting) is consistent across all menu items",
